Your Honour,

I stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of assault. I take full responsibility for my actions and the harm I have caused. I would like to sincerely apologize to the victim and their family for the distress and pain I have inflicted upon them.

During a moment of anger, I pushed my employee to the ground and kicked him in the stomach. The reason behind this was his grave error at work, which I believed would result in significant financial consequences for my company. While it does not excuse my actions, the intense frustration and concern for the well-being of my business clouded my judgment.

I deeply regret the harm I caused and the impact it has had on the victim's life and their loved ones. Immediately after the incident, I recognized the severity of my actions and acted swiftly to ensure the victim's safety and well-being. I brought him to the closest emergency room to ensure that he received the necessary medical attention.

I want to emphasize that this incident is completely out of character for me and is an isolated occurrence in an otherwise law-abiding life. I am a 40-year-old individual with no prior criminal record, and I have always strived to be a responsible member of society. I am truly remorseful for my behavior and the pain I have caused to those involved.

I humbly request the opportunity to express my sincere apologies to the victim and their family once more. I have offered to cover all remaining hospital bills as a gesture of my accountability for the consequences of my actions.

While I have not yet sought professional counseling, I fully acknowledge the need for personal growth in managing my emotions and addressing any potential issues related to anger management. It is my utmost intention to ensure that such a transgression never happens again.

Your Honour, I plead guilty and accept the gravity of my actions. I respectfully request your leniency and consideration in deciding an appropriate sentence. I am prepared to face the consequences of my actions and commit to rehabilitation. My earnest hope is to make amends and contribute positively to society once again.

Thank you for your attention.

